Here is some MATLAB code to learn per-exemplar distance functions
Tomasz Malisiewicz (tomasz@cmu.edu)
July 8th, 2008

-------------------------------------------------------

Per-Exemplar Distance Function Learning used in CVPR 2008 paper:
Tomasz Malisiewicz, Alexei A. Efros. Recognition by Association via Learning Per-exemplar Distances. In CVPR, June 2008.
http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~tmalisie/projects/cvpr08/

SVM in the Primal Code from Olivier Chapelle
http://www.kyb.tuebingen.mpg.de/bs/people/chapelle/primal/

Texton code comes from Berkeley Texton Codebase

-------------------------------------------------------

After features have been computed use the function:
learn_all_dfuns

Computing CVPR08 Segment Features Code in:
get14feats

Applying distance functions to new data, use function:
getdistmatrix_parts

Some synthetic data examples seen in:
testing/test_learn
